fields.name: Black Adam
fields.description: Nearly 5,000 years after he was bestowed with the almighty powers of the Egyptian gods-and imprisoned just as quickly-Black Adam (Johnson) is freed from his earthly tomb, ready to unleash his unique form of justice on the modern world.
fields.producer: Sohrab Noshirvani, Adam Sztykiel, Rory Haines

fields.name: Dune
fields.description: A noble family becomes embroiled in a war for control over the galaxy's most valuable asset while its heir becomes troubled by visions of a dark future.

fields.name: Doctor Strange
fields.description: While on a journey of physical and spiritual healing, a brilliant neurosurgeon is drawn into the world of the mystic arts.
fields.producer: Marvel Entertainment, Marvel Studios, Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures

fields.name: The Matrix-1
fields.description: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

fields.name: The Departed
fields.description: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

fields.name: Shutter Island
fields.description: In 1954, a U.S. Marshal investigates the disappearance of a murderer who escaped from a hospital for the criminally insane.

fields.name: The Shawshank Redemption
fields.description: Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

fields.name: Batman Begins
fields.description: After training with his mentor, Batman begins his fight to free crime-ridden Gotham City from corruption.
fields.producer: MTV Movie & TV Award for Best Movie, MORE

fields.name: Lucy
fields.description: A woman, accidentally caught in a dark deal, turns the tables on her captors and transforms into a merciless warrior evolved beyond human logic.

fields.name: Mr. & Mrs. Smith
fields.description: A bored married couple is surprised to learn that they are both assassins hired by competing agencies to kill each other.
fields.producer: MTV Movie & TV Award for Best Kiss, MORE

fields.name: Se7en
fields.description: Two detectives, a rookie and a veteran, hunt a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his motives.
fields.director: MTV Movie & TV Award for Best Villain, MORE

fields.name: Fight Club
fields.description: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soap maker form an underground fight club that evolves into much more.

fields.name: The Dark Knight
fields.description: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

fields.name: Now You See Me
fields.description: An F.B.I. Agent and an Interpol Detective track a team of illusionists who pull off bank heists during their performances, and reward their audiences with the money.
fields.producer: Alex Kurtzman, Boaz Yakin, Roberto Orci, Bobby Cohen

fields.name: Sherlock
fields.description: A modern update finds the famous sleuth and his doctor partner solving crime in 21st-century London.
fields.producer: Mark Gatiss, Steven Moffat, Sue Vertue, MORE
fields.director: Mark Gatiss, A.C. Doyle, Steven Moffat, Steve Thompson

fields.name: Dexter
fields.description: He's smart. He's lovable. He's Dexter Morgan, America's favorite serial killer, who spends his days solving crimes and nights committing them. Golden Globe winner Michael C. Hall stars in the hit SHOWTIME Original Series.

fields.name: True Detective
fields.description: Seasonal anthology series in which police investigations unearth the personal and professional secrets of those involved, both within and outside the law.

fields.name: Breaking Bad
fields.description: A chemistry teacher diagnosed with inoperable lung cancer turns to manufacturing and selling methamphetamine with a former student in order to secure his family's future.
fields.producer: Vince Gilligan, Michael Slovis, Colin Bucksey, MORE

fields.name: Better Call Saul
fields.description: The trials and tribulations of criminal lawyer Jimmy McGill in the years leading up to his fateful run-in with Walter White and Jesse Pinkman.

fields.name: Game of Thrones
fields.description: Nine noble families fight for control over the lands of Westeros, while an ancient enemy returns after being dormant for millennia.

fields.name: Winter Is Coming
fields.description: Eddard Stark is torn between his family and an old friend when asked to serve at the side of King Robert Baratheon; Viserys plans to wed his sister to a nomadic warlord in exchange for an army.

fields.name: The Kingsroad
fields.description: While Bran recovers from his fall, Ned takes only his daughters to King's Landing. Jon Snow goes with his uncle Benjen to the Wall. Tyrion joins them.

fields.name: Lord Snow
fields.description: Jon begins his training with the Night's Watch; Ned confronts his past and future at King's Landing; Daenerys finds herself at odds with Viserys.

fields.name: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
fields.description: Eddard investigates Jon Arryn's murder. Jon befriends Samwell Tarly, a coward who has come to join the Night's Watch.

fields.name: The Wolf and the Lion
fields.description: Catelyn has captured Tyrion and plans to bring him to her sister, Lysa Arryn, at the Vale, to be tried for his, supposed, crimes against Bran. Robert plans to have Daenerys killed, but Eddard refuses to be a part of it and quits.

fields.name: A Golden Crown
fields.description: While recovering from his battle with Jaime, Eddard is forced to run the kingdom while Robert goes hunting. Tyrion demands a trial by combat for his freedom. Viserys is losing his patience with Drogo.

fields.name: You Win or You Die
fields.description: Robert has been injured while hunting and is dying. Jon and the others finally take their vows to the Night's Watch. A man, sent by Robert, is captured for trying to poison Daenerys. Furious, Drogo vows to attack the Seven Kingdoms.

fields.name: The Pointy End
fields.description: The Lannisters press their advantage over the Starks; Robb rallies his father's northern allies and heads south to war; The White Walkers attack the Wall; Tyrion returns to his father with some new friends.

fields.name: Baelor
fields.description: Robb goes to war against the Lannisters. Jon finds himself struggling on deciding if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Drogo has fallen ill from a fresh battle wound. Daenerys is desperate to save him.

fields.name: Fire and Blood
fields.description: Robb vows to get revenge on the Lannisters. Jon must officially decide if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Daenerys says her final goodbye to Drogo.

fields.name: Unaired Pilot
fields.description: Invalided home from the war in Afghanistan, Dr. John Watson becomes roommates with the world's only "consulting detective," Sherlock Holmes. Within a day their friendship is forged and several murders are solved.

fields.name: A Study in Pink
fields.description: War vet Dr. John Watson returns to London in need of a place to stay. He meets Sherlock Holmes, a consulting detective, and the two soon find themselves digging into a string of serial "suicides."

fields.name: The Blind Banker
fields.description: Mysterious symbols and murders are showing up all over London, leading Sherlock and John to a secret Chinese crime syndicate called Black Lotus.

fields.name: The Great Game
fields.description: Mycroft needs Sherlock's help, but a remorseless criminal mastermind puts Sherlock on a distracting crime-solving spree via a series of hostage human bombs through which he speaks.
